radiographic_examinations.findings: Diffuse fatty infiltration of the liver without focal hepatic lesions, a nonobstructing stone (3 mm in diameter) in the interpolar region of the right kidney, surgical clips in the gallbladder fossa consistent with cholecystectomy, and degenerative changes in the visualized skeleton.
No evidence of pneumonia or pulmonary edema.
Minimal abnormal thickening of the endometrium (0.7 cm); normal uterine and ovarian dimensions.
